ZH: 我很幸运能够找到一份满意的工作。
EN: I am lucky to have found a job that I enjoy.

ZH: 这次考试我很幸运，全对了。
EN: I was lucky in the exam, I got everything right.

ZH: 幸运的是，他们平安抵达目的地。
EN: Fortunately, they arrived at their destination safely.

ZH: 他非常幸运，没有受伤。
EN: He was very lucky and wasn't injured.

ZH: 我们非常幸运，避过了那场风暴。
EN: We were very lucky to have avoided that storm.

ZH: 幸运女神总是眷顾着他。
EN: Lady Luck always smiles on him.

ZH: 要感谢幸运女神，他才取得了这场胜利。
EN: He owes his victory to Lady Luck.

ZH: 虽然付出了努力，但也需要一点幸运。
EN: While hard work pays off, a bit of luck is also necessary.

ZH: 幸运有时候真的会降临在你的身上。
EN: Luck can sometimes really come to you.

ZH: 幸运是那些勇敢者的伴侣。
EN: Luck is the companion of the brave.

ZH: 在逆境中抓住幸运的尾巴。
EN: Grasp the tail of luck in adversity.

ZH: 人生有时候是幸运与勇气的结合。
EN: Life is a combination of luck and courage.

ZH: 幸运的人生太枯燥，不如经历挫折。
EN: A life of constant luck is boring, it's better to experience setbacks.

ZH: 幸运总是垂青于那些敢于冒险的人。
EN: Luck always favors those who dare to take risks.

ZH: 体育比赛中，不仅靠实力，也需要幸运。
EN: In sports competitions, luck is needed in addition to strength.

ZH: 幸运总是倾向于团结合作的团队。
EN: Luck always favors teams that work together.

ZH: 幸运来临时，要好好把握。
EN: When luck comes, make the most of it.

ZH: 他的成功离不开幸运的因素。
EN: His success is not without luck.

ZH: 在人生的旅途中，幸运是最好的导航。
EN: In the journey of life, luck is the best navigation.

ZH: 幸运是一种难以言说的神秘力量。
EN: Luck is a mysterious force that is hard to describe.
